he%20last%2075%20years%2C%20that's%20only%20happened%20twice%2C%20Toomey%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20when%20the%20market%20recovered%20from%20its%20decline%20in%20the%20early%2080s%20and%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Nasdaq%20Composite%20on%20Friday%20notched%20its%20own%20rare%20milestone%2C%20hitting%20its%20longest%20win%20streak%20since%201992.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2254e05f69-7751-4a7f-a05c-c5bf9d49148a%5C%22%3E5.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20outperformed%20its%20historical%20average%20in%20April%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20last%20Friday%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20was%20up%209%25%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20month.%20That's%20above%20five%20times%20the%20index's%20historical%20average%2C%20with%20the%20index%20gaining%20an%20average%201.7%20percentage%20points%20for%20the%20month%20over%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20Toomey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-rally-technical-analysis-signals-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776764401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64082367066d7c296e97e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-rally-technical-analysis-signals-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jefferies%20outlined%20a%20handful%20of%20technical%20indicators%20that%20suggested%20the%20stock%20market%20rally%20has%20stalled.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jsor%40businessinsider.com%20(Jennifer%20Sor)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-rally-technical-analysis-signals-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20millennial%20who%20ditched%20my%20smartphone%20for%20a%20month.%20I%20made%20new%20friends%20and%20ended%20up%20keeping%20my%20flip%20phone.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221967%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maneesha%20Panja%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64f26a98bc8fdc096c790%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221475%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EManeesha%20Panja%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20tech%20product%20leader%2C%20swapped%20her%20smartphone%20for%20a%20flip%20phone.%20She%20hasn't%20switched%20back%20since.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EManeesha%20Panja%2C%2030%2C%20joined%20Month%20Offline%2C%20a%20program%20that%20syncs%20smartphone%20data%20to%20a%20flip%20phone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20spent%20a%20month%20using%20her%20flip%20phone%20and%20meeting%20with%20other%20members%20of%20the%20group.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20made%20new%20friends%20and%20had%20more%20time%20to%20read.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20keep%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappstinence-movement-tech-lovers-dumping-smartphones-age-of-dumb-phones-2025-5%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edumb%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Maneesha%20Panja%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20product%20leader%20at%20a%20small%20startup%20living%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20'90s%20and%20early%202000s.%20Many%20of%20my%20early%20memories%20of%20technology%20are%20associated%20with%20discovery%20and%20delight.%20I%20remember%20getting%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipod-bring-back-tim-cook-apple-survey-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20iPod%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20such%20a%20big%20deal%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20got%20older%2C%20my%20relationship%20with%20technology%20grew%20more%20complex.%20At%20first%2C%20social%20media%20was%20great%20because%20I%20could%20keep%20up%20with%20my%20high%20school%20friends%20while%20in%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20it%20got%20overwhelming.%20Social%20media%20went%20from%20something%20I%20used%20primarily%20to%20stay%20connected%20to%20friends%20to%20something%20I%20reached%20for%20even%20when%20I%20didn't%20want%20it%20%E2%80%94%20or%20when%20I%20wanted%20to%20ignore%20an%20unpleasant%20emotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20unlimited%20access%20to%20everything%20at%20any%20moment%20was%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20other%20things%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20like%20reading%20or%20creative%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphone-users-cant-live-without-camera-dumb-phone-light-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egive%20up%20my%20smartphone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20so%20helpful%20for%20checking%20my%20email%2C%20texting%20friends%2C%20and%20looking%20up%20directions.%20I%20also%20work%20as%20a%20product%20leader%20at%20a%20small%20startup%2C%20and%20couldn't%20completely%20separate%20myself%20from%20technology.%20App%20blockers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbricking-your-phone-analog-movement-the-new-dry-january-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBricking%20my%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%20didn't%20work%20for%20me%3B%20they%20felt%20like%20they%20went%20against%20the%20device's%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20welcome%20box%20from%20Month%20Offline.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64e2e3fecbb42897a1b29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221458%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20welcome%20box%20from%20Month%20Offline.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20about%20Month%20Offline%2C%20a%20roughly%20%2475%20program%2C%20when%20they%20hosted%20a%20phone-free%20event%20after%20a%20concert%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20went%20to.%20The%20program%20would%20help%20transfer%20my%20contacts%20to%20a%20flip%20phone%2C%20which%20I%20would%20use%20for%20a%20month%20alongside%20a%20cohort%20of%20people%20I'd%20meet%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20decided%20to%20sign%20up%20in%20January%2C%20even%20though%20we%20were%20nervous.%20He%20and%20I%20both%20had%20different%20things%20we%20wanted%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20program%2C%20but%20it%20all%20came%20down%20to%20the%20same%20reason%3A%20We%20wanted%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-no-smartphone-social-media-friends-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escreen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201ab883a-d187-4d4d-904c-20c934aaab86%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20worried%20about%20inviting%20friction%20into%20my%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20TCL%20flip%20phone%20with%20stickers%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64dfd367066d7c296ea0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20program%20gave%20participants%20a%20TCL%20flip%20phone%20with%20a%20camera%2C%20texting%2C%20and%20access%20to%20basic%20navigation%20tools.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20week%20before%20we%20started%20the%20program%2C%20I%20remember%20telling%20my%20husband%20I%20didn't%20feel%20ready.%20What%20if%20we%20postponed%20it%20for%20another%20month%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wondered%20how%20I%20would%20do%20my%20job%20or%20navigate%20the%20city%20without%20my%20smartphone.%20I%20wondered%20if%20I%20needed%20to%20invite%20those%20elements%20of%20friction%20into%20my%20life%20right%20now.%20Despite%20my%20reservations%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20at%20least%20commit%20to%20the%20first%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised%20to%20learn%20that%20the%20dumb%20phone%20we%20got%20through%20the%20program%20%E2%80%94%20a%20TCL%20FLIP%20Go%20%E2%80%94%20still%20had%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsamsung-bet-on-flip-phones-gains-momentum-against-apple-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esame%20perks%20as%20smartphones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20could%20still%20text%20my%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20even%20if%20they%20had%20iPhones.%20I%20could%20access%20basic%20navigation%20tools%20like%20Google%20Maps.%20Even%20the%20camera%20was%20surprisingly%20good%20for%20a%20flip%20phone.%20For%20work%2C%20I%20could%20use%20it%20for%20two-factor%20authentication%20via%20SMS-based%20codes%20for%20certain%20applications%2C%20such%20as%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maneesha%20Panja%20with%20her%20sister%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64d18367066d7c296e9fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221458%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPanja%20took%20a%20selfie%20with%20her%20sister%20using%20her%20flip%20phone.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20still%20some%20inconveniences%2C%20which%20I%20eventually%20learned%20to%20look%20at%20as%20benefits.%20For%20instance%2C%20I%20had%20to%20get%20used%20to%20buying%20and%20loading%20an%20OMNY%20card%20to%20use%20the%20subway%2C%20instead%20of%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmartphone-cell-wasnt-right-preteen-flip-phone-great-compromise-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etapping%20my%20smartphone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20missed%20the%20train%20a%20few%20times%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20times%2C%20I%20sat%20down%2C%20frustrated%20and%20bored.%20The%20next%20train%20that%20came%20wasn't%20the%20one%20I%20needed.%20I%20looked%20up%20at%20the%20train%20conductor%2C%20who%20just%20smiled%20and%20waved%20at%20me%2C%20and%20I%20waved%20back.%20That%20human%20connection%20just%20gave%20me%20so%20much%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20like%20I%20wasn't%20having%20those%20experiences%20before%2C%20but%20having%20this%20flip%20phone%20gave%20me%20space%20to%20appreciate%20these%20moments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9927333-fd1f-4093-89c6-db972d14dfbc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20made%20new%20friends%20and%20spent%20more%20quality%20time%20with%20my%20husband%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222212%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maneesha%20Panja%20with%20her%20friend%20and%20husband.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64d51367066d7c296e9ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221659%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPanja%20with%20her%20friend%20(left)%20and%20husband.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMonth%20Offline%20provided%20us%20with%20suggestions%20to%20help%20us%20adjust%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-creating-own-versions-of-landlines-with-cellphones-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elife%20without%20smartphones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20suggestion%20was%20to%20create%20an%20%26quot%3Binternet%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20just%20like%20the%20one%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20when%20I%20had%20a%20family%20computer.%20I%20even%20bought%20a%20printer%20and%20started%20printing%20out%20drafts%20of%20my%20writing%20to%20hand-edit%20them%2C%20instead%20of%20spending%20more%20time%20at%20the%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20the%20program%20was%20the%20built-in%20community.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20assigned%20two%20buddies%20called%20flipmates%2C%20who%20we'd%20meet%20with%20at%20least%20once%20a%20week%2C%20with%20the%20option%20to%20keep%20hanging%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20becoming%20good%20friends%20with%20my%20flipmates.%20We%20hung%20out%20together%2C%20including%20one%20time%20when%20we%20all%20got%20up%20early%20on%20a%20Saturday%20morning%20and%20went%20to%20the%20Transit%20Museum%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20since%20none%20of%20us%20had%20ever%20been.%20As%20soon%20as%20we%20left%20the%20museum%2C%20a%20snowstorm%20started%2C%20and%20we%20all%20took%20photos%20with%20a%20disposable%20camera.%20I%20just%20couldn't%20imagine%20having%20that%20experience%20without%20this%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222260%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Panja%20taking%20photos%20of%20her%20flipmates%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64dcc3fecbb42897a1b23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221695%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPanja%20taking%20photos%20of%20her%20flipmates.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20nice%20memory%20was%20when%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20went%20to%20East%20Williamsburg%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20which%20we're%20not%20as%20familiar%20with.%20We%20got%20lost%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20train%20and%20ended%20up%20at%20a%20bar%20we'd%20been%20to%20once.%20We%20decided%20to%20stop%20in%20and%20hang%20out%20for%20a%20bit.%20We%20realized%20we%20never%20do%20that.%20Normally%2C%20we'd%20plan%20an%20evening%20ahead%20of%20time.%20Not%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-anti-social-media-event-jonathan-haidt-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20using%20smartphones%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20so%20much%20spontaneity%20and%20more%20quality%20time%20to%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20also%20invited%20us%20to%20work%20on%20art%20projects%20to%20present%20at%20the%20end%2C%20things%20we%20wanted%20to%20accomplish%20without%20the%20distraction%20of%20smartphones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20we%20had%20a%20party%20with%20a%20huge%20turnout.%20Someone%20read%20the%20play%20that%20they%20had%20worked%20on.%20Someone%20made%20a%20film%2C%20another%20person%20wrote%20a%20story.%20I%20made%20a%20painting.%20It%20was%20a%20visual%20artifact%20of%20the%20time%20we%20spent%20together%2C%20off%20our%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298811afa-006b-49af-a1b3-d10c43895e14%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20flip%20phone%20makes%20me%20less%20anxious%20and%20more%20present%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223130%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20sledding%20in%20Prospect%20Park%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e64ccb3fecbb42897a1b12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222075%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPanja%20loved%20the%20spontaneity%20of%20not%20having%20a%20smartphone%2C%20so%20she%20kept%20using%20her%20flip%20phone%20after%20the%20program%20ended.%3Cp%3EManeesha%20Panja%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20I'm%20done%20with%20the%20program%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20keep%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyondr-ceo-graham-dugoni-phone-pouch-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20flip%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20I%20still%20have%20my%20smartphone%2C%20I%20pay%20a%20%2424%20monthly%20subscription%20to%20the%20dumb%20phone%20that%20gives%20me%20access%20to%20the%20hardware%20and%20phone%20line.%20Since%20the%20program%2C%20TCL%20now%20also%20offers%20limited%20Uber%20capabilities%2C%20making%20it%20even%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20still%20need%20to%20use%20my%20smartphone%20for%20work%3B%20two-factor%20authentication%20can%20be%20more%20seamless%20for%20certain%20apps%20than%20on%20my%20flip%20phone.%20Still%2C%20I%20deleted%20all%20my%20apps%20other%20than%20the%20ones%20I%20strictly%20need%20for%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20using%20my%20flip%20phone%2C%20I%20feel%20more%20connected%20to%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20than%20ever%2C%20which%20is%20so%20ironic%2C%20since%20so%20much%20of%20the%20phone%20reduces%20your%20ability%20to%20be%20available%20all%20the%20time.%20I%20call%20my%20friends%20more.%20I%20set%20aside%20time%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20them%20in%20person.%20I%20wasn't%20doing%20that%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.