-john-ternus-replacing-tim-cook-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJohn%20Ternus%20takes%20over%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cook%20will%20remain%20as%20executive%20chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Cook%2C%20Apple%20has%20built%20a%20tightly%20integrated%20ecosystem%20of%20products%20and%20services%20that%20shapes%20how%20consumers%20engage%20with%20the%20brand.%20While%20the%20iPhone%20%E2%80%94%20launched%20under%20Jobs%20%E2%80%94%20remains%20its%20main%20revenue%20driver%2C%20an%20expanded%20services%20lineup%20that%20Cook%20shepherded%2C%20along%20with%20devices%20like%20the%20Apple%20Watch%2C%20has%20helped%20sustain%20its%20relevance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20became%20CEO%20in%202011%2C%20succeeding%20Apple's%20late%20cofounder%20and%20inheriting%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20companies%2C%20known%20for%20iconic%20product%20launches%20and%20flashy%20presentations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Jobs%20is%20mostly%20closely%20associated%20with%20the%20iPhone%2C%20Cook%20has%20overseen%20both%20wildly%20successful%20hits%20and%20notable%20misses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20look%20at%20pivotal%20products%20from%20Cook's%20time%20as%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EiPad%20Mini%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22iPad%20Mini%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e69ece367066d7c296ed3e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222257%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20iteration%20of%20the%20iPad%20Mini%20came%20out%20in%202012.%20It%20was%20a%20smaller%2C%20lighter%20version%20of%20Apple's%20original%20iPad%20and%20sold%20for%20%24329%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20allowed%20Apple%20to%20compete%20with%20lower-cost%20tablets%20while%20appealing%20to%20users%20who%20prioritized%20convenience%2C%20reading%2C%20and%20one-handed%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EiPad%20Pro%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20al