ibility%20to%20work%20from%20home%20in%20certain%20circumstances%2C%20his%20manager%20strictly%20enforced%20the%20company's%20five-day%20office%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gupta%2C%20the%20shift%20back%20to%20the%20office%20has%20worked%20in%20his%20favor%20%E2%80%94%20he%20lives%20about%20a%20seven-minute%20walk%20from%20the%20office.%20He%20pays%20around%20%242%2C700%20a%20month%2C%20including%20parking%2C%20for%20his%20one-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20and%20said%20that%20while%20there%20were%20cheaper%20options%20farther%20away%2C%20being%20close%20was%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20short%20commute%20has%20allowed%20me%20to%20focus%20on%20building%20my%20career%20instead%20of%20feeling%20drained%20from%20getting%20to%20and%20from%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Gupta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0b10812-c6c6-4367-a551-3ea9a15e7050%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20is%20reshaping%20how%20employees%20do%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20said%20he%20has%20been%20encouraged%20to%20use%20AI%20tools%20but%20hasn't%20been%20required%20to%20do%20so.%20For%20him%2C%20AI%20has%20become%20the%20most%20efficient%20way%20to%20get%20work%20done%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it%20can%20feel%20%26quot%3Bsoul-sucking%26quot%3B%20at%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20spend%20most%20of%20my%20time%20talking%20to%20AI%20agents%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chen.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20really%20imagine%20going%20through%20a%20day%20at%20Amazon%20without%20using%20AI%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%2C%20Amazon%20has%20made%20multibillion-dollar%20investments%20in%20Anthropic%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20plans%20to%20spend%20up%20to%20%24200%20billion%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-spending-plan-capex-stuns-wall-street-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eits%20AI%20buildout%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20Last%20year%2C%20Jassy%20said%20he%20expected%20efficiency%20gains%20from%20AI%20to%20eventually%20%26quot%3Breduce%26quot%3B%20the%20size%20of%20the%20company's%20corporate%20workforce.%20Some%20employees%20are%20now%20evaluated%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20how%20frequently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-amazons-hardcore-culture-reset-day-1-roots-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20use%20AI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20LA-based%20former%20product%20manager%20said%20he%20saw%20significant%20productivity%20gains%20for%20software%20engineers%2C%20but%20more%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bmixed%20bag%26quot%3B%20for%20other%20roles%2C%20like%20his%20own.%20While%20AI%20helped%20with%20tasks%20like%20writing%2C%20he%20said%20outputs%20were%20not%20always%20sufficiently%20reviewed%2C%20resulting%20in%20occasional%20errors%20across%20documents%2C%20emails%2C%20and%20Slack%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20AI%20became%20a%20frequent%20topic%20of%20conversation%20at%20work%2C%20and%20that%20many%20colleagues%20shared%20concerns%20about%20facing%20scrutiny%20or%20falling%20behind%20professionally%20if%20they%20didn't%20use%20the%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20a%20dynamic%20that%20shaped%20how%20they%20approached%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20fear%20of%20irrelevance%20that%20was%20causing%20most%20adoption%2C%20rather%20than%20excitement%20for%20technological%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJane%20Zhang%20contributed%20to%20reporting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-layoffs-artificial-intelligence-return-to-office-tech-jobs-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776762061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69dfa8c7777ecc79d62f4eb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-layoffs-artificial-intelligence-return-to-office-tech-jobs-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon%20employees%20say%20layoffs%2C%20AI%2C%20and%20return-to-office%20rules%20have%20reshaped%20their%20jobs%20in%20recent%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-layoffs-artificial-intelligence-return-to-office-tech-jobs-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20new%20fault%20line%20has%20emerged%20inside%20Google%3A%20The%20Claude%20haves%20and%20have-nots%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226759%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20DeepMind%20CEO%20Demis%20Hassabis%20speaks%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e674df367066d7c296eb33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224508%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20DeepMind%20CEO%20Demis%20Hassabis.%3Cp%3EWEF%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20Google%20DeepMind%20employees%20use%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20for%20coding%20internally.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMost%20Google%20employees%20are%20only%20permitted%20to%20use%20the%20company's%20internal%20Gemini%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20divide%20is%20causing%20tensions%20as%20Google%20pressures%20more%20employees%20to%20adopt%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20divide%20has%20emerged%20within%20Google%3A%20those%20allowed%20to%20use%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20and%20those%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-department-defense-military-contract-ai-deepmind-national-security-deals-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20DeepMind%3C%2Fa%3E%20employees%20in%20recent%20months%20have%20been%20given%20access%20to%20the%20Claude%20AI%20tool%20for%20coding%20purposes%2C%20according%20to%20three%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGooglers%20are%20generally%20prohibited%20from%20using%20tools%20that%20aren't%20either%20made%20by%20Google%20or%20tailored%20specifically%20for%20internal%20use.%20Meanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-boom-more-software-shipped-no-hit-quality-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClaude%20has%20become%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20AI%20coding%20tools%20across%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20let%20Google%20DeepMind%20employees%20use%20Claude%20has%20irked%20engineers%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20company%2C%20who%20are%20only%20allowed%20to%20use%20Google's%20internal%20Gemini%20AI%20models%20for%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20feel%20that%20Google's%20internal%20models%20aren't%20as%20good%20as%20Claude%20for%20coding%2C%20two%20of%20the%20people%20said.%20Giving%20some%20staff%20access%20to%20Claude%20has%20created%20tensions%2C%20as%20Google%20is%20telling%20more%20employees%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20engineers%20have%20been%20given%20specific%20AI%20goals%20that%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-ai-adoption-non-technical-software-engineer-performance-review-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efactored%20into%20performance%20reviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20these%20employees%20are%20being%20told%20they're%20not%20only%20expected%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20generate%20code%2C%20but%20to%20build%20tools%20that%20make%20their%20processes%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20keeps%20its%20engineers%20on%20internal%20tools%20for%20various%20reasons.%20Much%20of%20its%20internal%20infrastructure%20is%20custom-built.%20It%20also%20believes%20dogfooding%20%E2%80%94%20where%20employees%20test%20and%20use%20products%20they%20launch%20to%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20can%20help%20them%20improve%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20tech%20companies%20allow%20their%20employees%20to%20use%20external%20AI%20models.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-week-employee-training-claude-agents-vibe-coding-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%20employees%20can%20use%20Claude%3C%2Fa%3E%20internally%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229cd95188-8fb6-4ef9-8952-e45159f2c8af%5C%22%3EThe%20Google%20DeepMind%20CEO%20snaps%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-yegge-google-ai-adoption-curve-demis-hassabis-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESteve%20Yegge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20computer%20programmer%20and%20blogger%2C%20posted%20on%20X%20about%20Google's%20AI%20adoption.%20He%20said%20he%20spoke%20to%20a%20Google%20director%2C%20who%20told%20him%20the%20company's%20internal%20AI%20adoption%20was%20lagging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20TL%3BDR%20is%20that%20Google%20engineering%20appears%20to%20have%20the%20same%20AI%20adoption%20footprint%20as%20John%20Deere%2C%20the%20tractor%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20sparked%20plenty%20of%20discussion%20and%20solicited%20a%20blunt%20response%20from%20Google%20DeepMind%20CEO%20Demis%20Hassabis%3A%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20tell%20your%20buddy%20to%20do%20some%20actual%20work%20and%20to%20stop%20spreading%20absolute%20nonsense.%20This%20post%20is%20completely%20false%20and%20just%20pure%20clickbait.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYegge%20posted%20again%20on%20Monday%2C%20saying%20he'd%20heard%20from%20some%20Google%20employees%20who%20corroborated%20his%20claims.%20Yegge%20also%20said%20that%20some%20DeepMind%20engineers%20use%20Claude%2C%20while%20engineers%20across%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20company%20aren't%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20question%20of%20equalizing%20access%20came%20up%20internally%2C%20the%20proposed%20response%20was%20to%20remove%20Claude%20for%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20which%20DeepMind%20objected%20to%20so%20strongly%20that%20several%20engineers%20reportedly%20threatened%20to%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20something%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ahlangley%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehlangley%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20628-228-1836.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20non-work%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-ai-tool-divide-internal-tensions-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776762001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e684513fecbb42897a1cda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-ai-tool-divide-internal-tensions-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Google%20puts%20the%20pressure%20on%20employees%20to%20adopt%20AI%2C%20some%20are%20irked%20that%20their%20colleagues%20are%20allowed%20to%20use%20Anthropic's%20Claude.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hlangley%40businessinsider.com%20(Hugh%20Langley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-ai-tool-divide-internal-tensions-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aishwarya%20pick