tive%20chairman%2C%20built%20up%20an%20unprecedented%20record%20of%20success%20over%20his%20tenure%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-s-record-of-success-some-numerical-highlights-126042100514_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Workplace%20fairness%20laws%20are%20making%20work%20less%20fair%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20three%20business%20people%20speaking%20behind%20a%20foggy%20glassy%20door%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e690b2367066d7c296ec79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20Song%20Ma%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20finance%20and%20entrepreneurship%20at%20Yale%2C%20found%20himself%20torn%20between%20two%20competing%20ideas%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-loyalty-corporate-america-dysfunction-employers-employees-att-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20was%20that%20the%20%23MeToo%20movement%20had%20generated%20a%20powerful%20wave%20of%20reforms%20to%20protect%20victims%20of%20abuse.%20Starting%20in%202018%2C%20states%20including%20California%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Washington%20had%20passed%20laws%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsign-employee-nda-nondisclosure-agreement-job-study-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweaken%20non-disclosure%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20had%20long%20been%20used%20to%20silence%20victims%20of%20harassment%20at%20work.%20In%202022%2C%20Congress%20passed%20the%20Speak%20Out%20Act%2C%20which%20prevents%20employers%20from%20being%20able%20to%20demand%20workers%20to%20sign%20NDAs%20preemptively%2C%20before%20an%20incident%20or%20dispute%20occurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20were%20reforms%20nearly%20everyone%20cheered%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ma.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20good%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20other%20idea%20was%20that%20these%20laws%20may%20have%20backfired%2C%20and%20made%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-girl-boss-women-musk-zuckerberg-dimon-alpha-male-backlash-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworse%20for%20women%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20economists%2C%20we've%20learned%20that%20well-intentioned%20labor%20regulations%20don't%20always%20produce%20the%20outcomes%20we%20hope%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20After%20the%20Americans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%20came%20into%20effect%20in%201990%2C%20he%20notes%2C%20employment%20among%20disabled%20workers%20%3Cem%3Edeclined%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20some%20employers%20avoided%20hiring%20them%20to%20sidestep%20compliance%20costs.%20Similarly%2C%20so-called%20Ban%20the%20Box%20laws%2C%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20with%20criminal%20records%20get%20hired%2C%20ended%20up%20hurting%20young%20Black%20men%2C%20because%20employers%20fell%20back%20on%20what%20Ma%20calls%20%26quot%3Bcruder%20demographic%20proxies.%26quot%3B%20Because%20of%20harmful%20racial%20and%20gender%20stereotypes%2C%20Ma%20explains%2C%20hiring%20managers%20drew%20the%20conclusion%20that%20a%20Black%20man%20applying%20for%20a%20job%20was%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20criminal%20conviction%20than%20a%20different%20applicant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20to%20test%20whether%20a%20similar%20dynamic%20was%20playing%20out%20with%20NDA%20bans%2C%20Ma%20decided%20to%20look%20at%20startups.%20For%20one%2C%20%26quot%3BThey're%20crucial%20for%20innovation%20and%20job%20creation%2C%20yet%20often%20lack%20formal%20HR%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20He%20also%20knew%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffemale-founders-report-sexual-harassment-while-seeking-vc-funding-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharassment%20had%20been%20well-documented%20in%20the%20startup%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Ma%20and%20his%20collaborators%20published%20a%20paper%20with%20his%20findings%3A%20NDA%20bans%20weren't%20always%20living%20up%20to%20their%20advocates'%20expectations.%20Startups%20based%20in%20states%20that%20had%20implemented%20NDA-weakening%20laws%20hired%20about%208%25%20fewer%20women%20per%20year%20than%20startups%20in%20states%20that%20hadn't%20passed%20those%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20meaningful%20when%20you%20consider%20the%20average%20startup%20in%20our%20sample%20hires%20just%20over%20one%20woman%20per%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20effect%20appeared%20immediately%2C%20persisted%20for%20years%2C%20and%20concentrated%20exactly%20where%20you'd%20expect%20if%20firms%20were%20minimizing%20perceived%20legal%20risk%3A%20among%20junior%20women%20and%20in%20small%2C%20male-dominated%20startups%20with%20weaker%20internal%20safeguards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20bluntly%2C%20companies%20were%20once%20again%20sidestepping%20potential%20repercussions%20of%20regulation%20by%20simply%20not%20hiring%20people%20who%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20new%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENDA%20bans%20also%20aren't%20the%20only%20recent%20employment%20laws%20designed%20to%20create%20more%20equitable%20workplaces%20that%20have%20fallen%20short%20and%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20worst%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20even%20backfired.%20Another%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-transparency-laws-fail-salary-wages-sharing-taboo-income-employees-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emandating%20employers%20to%20post%20salary%20ranges%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20The%20Equal%20Pay%20for%20Equal%20Work%20Act%20went%20into%20effect%20in%20Colorado.%20New%20York%20and%20California%20both%20passed%20related%20laws%20the%20following%20year.%20States%20including%20Maryland%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20Nevada%2C%20and%20Rhode%20Island%20have%20adopted%20similar%20measures%20aimed%20at%20making%20pay%20negotiations%20less%20opaque.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20hailed%20as%20promising%20steps%20toward%20a%20more%20equitable%20workplace%2C%20largely%20because%2C%20as%20research%20shows%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-pay-transparency-jobs-income-taboo-equity-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20underpinned%20pay%20gaps%20in%20both%20gender%20and%20race.%20In%20many%20workplaces%2C%20employees%20have%20historically%20been%20discouraged%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-database-google-goldman-amazon-how-much-top-jobs-pay-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscussing%20salaries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20unequal%20pay%20for%20similar%20roles%20to%20go%20unnoticed%20for%20years%2C%20or%20even%20decades.%20Women%20who%20work%20full-time%20in%20the%20US%20earn%20around%2083%25%20of%20what%20men%20do%2C%20a%20figure%20that's%20hardly%20changed%20in%20recent%20decades.%20For%20Black%20and%20Latina%20women%2C%20the%20gap%20is%20considerably%20wider%20at%20about%2066%25%20and%2058%25%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20here%20too%2C%20transparency%20alone%20has%20proven%20to%20be%20an%20imperfect%20solution%20to%20a%20complex%20and%20entrenched%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20issue%20is%20that%20salary%20range%20laws%20currently%20offer%20little%20guidance%20on%20how%20wide%20or%20narrow%20the%20ranges%20should%20be.%20And%20that%20detail%2C%20research%20suggests%2C%20can%20significantly%20shape%20how%20candidates%20respond%20to%20job%20postings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlice%20Lee%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20Cornell%2C%20is%20part%20of%20a%20team%20that%20analyzed%20almost%2010%20million%20US%20job%20postings.%20They%20found%20that%20the%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-salaries-revealed-how-much-engineers-researchers-made-in-2025-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esalary%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20spanned%20about%20%2438%2C000.%20But%20variation%20was%20enormous%3A%20some%20listings%20covered%20%2420%2C000%2C%20while%20others%20stretched%20well%20past%20%24100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20discovery%20got%20Lee%20thinking%20about%20whether%20the%20width%20of%20a%20posted%20range%20might%20affect%20who%20decides%20to%20apply%20and%20how%20they%20subsequently%20negotiate%2C%20especially%20%26quot%3Bgiven%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-minimize-themselves-job-interviews-career-breaks-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%2C%20on%20average%2C%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20averse%20to%20financial%20uncertainty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20When%20Lee%20and%20her%20colleagues%20subsequently%20studied%20this%2C%20her%20suspicions%20were%20corroborated%3A%20Women%20indeed%20show%20a%20stronger%20preference%20than%20men%20for%20jobs%20with%20narrower%20salary%20ranges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWider%20posted%20ranges%20were%20associated%20with%20lower%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20even%20after%20accounting%20for%20firm%20size%20and%20other%20factors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20explains.%20%26quot%3BThat%20suggested%20this%20isn't%20just%20a%20pattern%20that%20shows%20up%20in%20controlled%20settings%20but%20one%20that%20may%20be%20shaping%20real%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-new-grads-can-stand-out-in-slow-job-market-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%20So%20yes%2C%20she%20concluded%2C%20the%20current%20approach%20to%20transparency%20may%20be%20perpetuating%20the%20very%20pay%20gaps%20the%20laws%20were%20designed%20to%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20interviewed%20half%20a%20dozen%20women%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-taking-pay-cuts-huge-numbers-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20whom%20requested%20anonymity%20for%20fear%20it%20might%20disadvantage%20them%20in%20future%20salary%20negotiations%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20said%20they%20weren't%20surprised%20by%20these%20results%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20company%20posts%20a%20huge%20salary%20range%2C%20it%20makes%20me%20feel%20like%20they're%20ticking%20a%20box%20rather%20than%20actually%20complying%20with%20a%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%2039-year%20old%20woman%20who%20works%20in%20healthcare%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20me%20wonder%20what%20other%20rules%20and%20laws%20that%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20bypass.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20does%20show%20that%20pay%20range%20transparency%20can%20help%20close%20wage%20gaps%20%E2%80%94%20if%20the%20range%20is%20not%20too%20big%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20if%20pay%20offers%20fall%20within%20the%20advertised%20range.%20But%20the%20complications%20don't%20stop%20at%20hiring.%20Even%20in%20fully%20transparent%20environments%2C%20unintended%20consequences%20can%20emerge.%20Research%20published%20last%20year%20by%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Riverside%2C%20for%20example%2C%20found%20that%20when%20workers%20learn%20how%20their%20pay%20compares%20to%20their%20peers%2C%20their%20sense%20of%20entitlement%20can%20shift%20sharply%20depending%20on%20where%20they%20rank.%20Those%20near%20the%20top%20reported%20increased%20confidence%2C%20while%20lower-ranked%20employees%20often%20felt%20demoralized%20%E2%80%94%20and%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20ask%20for%20raises.%20This%20dynamic%20can%20also%20affect%20performance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-layoffs-cuts-underperformers-sra-spring-summer-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELower-ranked%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20research%20shows%2C%20may%20feel%20less%20motivated%20to%20improve%20or%20collaborate%20after%20learning%20they%20earn%20less%20than%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20also%20found%20that%20greater%20pay%20transparency%20can%20reduce%20workers'%20bargaining%20power%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20push%20down%20average%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20employment%20laws%20designed%20to%20bolster%20equity%20are%20at%20times%20exacerbating%20inequality%2C%20what%20is%20to%20be%20done%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20and%20leadership%20consultant%20Ruchika%20T.%20Malhotra%20says%20that%20one%20big%20problem%20is%20that%20managers%20are%20still%20failing%20to%20understand%20that%20making%20organizations%20fair%20and%20equitable%20benefits%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20research%20demonstrating%20that%20more%20inclusive%20workplaces%20translate%20into%20happier%20employees%2C%20better%20staff%20retention%2C%20and%20a%20healthier%20bottom%20line%2C%20%26quot%3Bmany%20organizations%20still%20operate%20with%20a%20zero-sum%20mindset%20%E2%80%94%20this%20idea%20that%20if%20one%20group%20benefits%2C%20another%20loses%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Malhotra.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20incorrect%20belief%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20increasing%20equity%20somehow%20disadvantages%20men%2C%20even%20though%20there's%20so%20much%20data%20showing%20otherwise.%26quot%3B%20In%202024%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%20predicted%20that%20closing%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-gap-by-state-how-much-women-and-men-earn-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20gaps%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20work%20and%20pay%20could%20increase%20global%20GDP%20by%20more%20than%20a%20fifth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20how%20deep-rooted%20this%20belief%20is%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20legislation%20alone%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20mindset%20shift%2C%20she%20says.%20Instead%20managers%20need%20to%20experience%20firsthand%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebenefits%20of%20fairer%20workplaces%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20understand%20that%20the%20laws%20are%20not%20designed%20to%20punish%20them%20but%20to%20help%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20a%20real%2C%20internal%20commitment%20to%20want%20to%20fix%20issues%20of%20unfairness%20and%20inequality%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Malhotra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESong%20Ma%20of%20Yale%20says%20that%20regulation%20has%20to%20be%20paired%20with%20%26quot%3Binstitutional%26quot%3B%20support%20in%20order%20to%20be%20effective.%20His%20research%20shows%20that%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-tech-workers-nda-culture-silence-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENDA%20bans%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20passed%2C%20female%20hiring%20particularly%20decreased%20in%20startups%20that%20didn't%20have%20a%20fleshed-out%20HR%20department.%20In%20larger%20firms%20in%20which%20those%20resources%20are%20more%20established%2C%20though%2C%20there%20was%20no%20reduction%20in%20female%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lesson%20isn't%20'don't%20ban%20NDAs%2C'%26quot%3B%20says%20Ma.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20legal%20reforms%20work%20best%20when%20firms%20have%20the%20infrastructure%20to%20absorb%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20his%20research%20also%20revealed%20some%20encouraging%20effects%20from%20new%20NDA%20legislation.%20Although%20it%20led%20to%20fewer%20women%20getting%20hired%2C%20it%20also%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20reaching%20managerial%20positions.%20%26quot%3BFollowing%20NDA%20reforms%2C%20startups%20experience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-have-more-direct-reports-after-great-flattening-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20male-manager%20turnover%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20and%20his%20colleagues%20wrote%20in%20the%20paper.%20This%20was%20perhaps%2C%20the%20researchers%20speculated%2C%20due%20to%20firms%20filling%20vacancies%20left%20by%20male%20managers%2C%20who%20%E2%80%94%20because%20of%20the%20NDA%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20pay%20transparency%20laws%2C%20Alice%20Lee%20of%20Cornell%20says%20that%20salary%20ranges%20alone%20aren't%20enough.%20If%20she%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bmagic%20wand%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20she%20would%20%26quot%3Brequire%20employers%20to%20supplement%20posted%20salary%20ranges%20with%20clear%20contextual%20information%20about%20compensation.%26quot%3B%20In%20her%20research%20she%20tested%20this%20approach%20by%20providing%20job%20applicants%20with%20their%20desired%20role's%20typical%20starting%20salary%20and%20how%20that%20particular%20employer%20tends%20to%20determine%20what%20to%20offer.%20In%20cases%20in%20which%20that%20information%20was%20provided%2C%20she%20explains%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20gender%20gap%20in%20application%20preferences%20effectively%20disappeared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20would%20also%20help%2C%20Lee%20says%2C%20would%20be%20stricter%20rules%20on%20the%20ranges.%20In%202025%20New%20Jersey%20proposed%20a%20law%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20caps%20the%20width%20of%20posted%20ranges%20at%2060%25%20of%20the%20minimum%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20should%20also%20consider%20whether%20one%20single%20wide%20range%20genuinely%20reflects%20one%20role%20at%20one%20level%2C%20or%20whether%20that%20range%20is%20really%20bundling%20together%20different%20positions%20that%20would%20be%20better%20served%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-isnt-killing-software-coding-jobs-booming-trueup-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%2C%20more%20precise%20postings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20is%20cautiously%20optimistic.%20%26quot%3BThese%20laws%20represent%20genuine%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20these%20policies%20should%20focus%20not%20just%20on%20whether%20employers%20disclose%20a%20range%2C%20but%20on%20whether%20that%20disclosure%20is%20actually%20useful%20to%20the%20people%20it's%20intended%20to%20serve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20while%20many%20laws%20represent%20a%20step%20towards%20a%20fairer%20workplace%2C%20ticking%20a%20box%20is%20never%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20lasting%20change.%20External%20regulation%20will%20almost%20always%20fall%20short%20without%20internal%20intention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjosie-cox%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJosie%20Cox%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20worked%20for%20publications%20like%20Reuters%2C%20The%20Independent%2C%20and%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal.%20She%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BWomen%20Money%20Power%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-fairness-metoo-nda-bans-pay-transparency-backfiring-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776759181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e690e0a98bc8fdc096c9ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-fairness-metoo-nda-bans-pay-transparency-backfiring-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%23MeToo%20movement%20u