org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwaiti-actress-hayat-al-fahad-dies-at-78-veteran-gulf-screen-icon-passes-away-after-prolonged-illness%2Famp_articleshow%2F130411576.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwaiti-actress-hayat-al-fahad-dies-at-78-veteran-gulf-screen-icon-passes-away-after-prolonged-illness%2Famp_articleshow%2F130411576.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tim%20Cook%20built%20Apple's%20China%20era%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Cook%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e710103fecbb42897a203d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETim%20Cook's%20China%20strategy%20has%20powered%20the%20company's%20rise%20and%20now%20shapes%20its%20biggest%20risks.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETim%20Cook%20left%20his%20mark%20on%20the%20tech%20world%2C%20but%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20parts%20of%20his%20legacy%20lies%20in%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECook%20turned%20China%20into%20the%20backbone%20of%20Apple's%20global%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20Cook%20made%20China%20central%20to%20Apple's%20growth%2C%20turning%20risks%20into%20rewards.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Tim%20Cook's%20defining%20legacies%20is%20clear%3A%20He%20made%20China%20the%20backbone%20of%20Apple's%20global%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20announced%20on%20Monday%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-apple-ceo-john-ternus-replacing-tim-cook-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Ternus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20hardware%20engineering%20and%20long%20seen%20as%20Cook's%20likely%20successor%2C%20will%20take%20over%20as%20chief%20executive.%20Cook%20will%20remain%20as%20executive%20chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook's%20bet%20on%20China%20as%20the%20engine%20of%20Apple's%20rise%20helped%20shape%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20valuable%20companies.%20It%20also%20bound%20Apple's%20fortunes%20to%20a%20market%20that%20is%20as%20much%20a%20source%20of%20risk%20as%20it%20is%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20Cook%20made%20China%20core%20to%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECook%20scaled%20China%20into%20Apple's%20factory%20floor%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225084%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Employees%20working%20at%20a%20Foxconn%20factory%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e724a1a98bc8fdc096ccdc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223322%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EVCG%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Cook%20joined%20Apple%20in%201998%2C%20the%20company%20was%20clawing%20its%20way%20back%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-comeback-story-2010-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20brink%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%201997%2C%20cofounder%20Steve%20Jobs%20said%20Apple%20was%20about%2090%20days%20from%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20was%20brought%20in%20to%20fix%20operations%2C%20and%20he%20made%20a%20radical%20call%3A%20shifting%20production%20to%20China.%20A%20network%20of%20manufacturers%20in%20that%20country%20was%20not%20only%20cheaper%2C%20but%20faster%20and%20easier%20to%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20moment%20of%20this%20shift%20came%20when%20Cook%20met%20Terry%20Gou%20around%202000.%20Gou's%20company%2C%20Foxconn%2C%20would%20go%20on%20to%20become%20Apple's%20key%20manufacturing%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20assembling%20early%20iPods%20after%20their%202001%20debut%20and%20later%20playing%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20producing%20the%20iPhone%20when%20it%20launched%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20China%20was%20also%20pushing%20to%20move%20up%20the%20value%20chain%2C%20encouraging%20factories%20to%20produce%20more%20advanced%20electronics%20instead%20of%20low-cost%20goods%20like%20toys%20and%20garments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20manufacture%20in%20China%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20payoff.%20By%20the%20time%20the%20iPhone%20era%20took%20off%2C%20Apple%20could%20launch%20products%20globally%20at%20a%20scale%20and%20speed%20competitors%20struggled%20to%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHe%20expanded%20Apple's%20business%20inside%20China%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20store%20in%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e725133fecbb42897a2050%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Ecredit%20should%20read%20CFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20has%20been%20credited%20with%20making%20China%20an%20important%20consumer%20market%20for%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20Apple%20officially%20entered%20China%20with%20a%20Shanghai-based%20trading%20company.%20By%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20it%20was%20rapidly%20expanding%20its%20retail%20footprint%2C%20opening%20stores%20in%20major%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20breakthroughs%20came%20in%202013%2C%20when%20Apple%20struck%20a%20deal%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-deal-with-china-mobile-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina%20Mobile%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20the%20world's%20largest%20carrier%20by%20subscribers.%20The%20partnership%20gave%20the%20iPhone%20access%20to%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20potential%20customers%20and%20marked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-losing-grip-tech-supply-chain-tsmc-nvidia-foxconn-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20turning%20point%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20Apple's%20presence%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20this%20as%20bringing%20the%20world's%20best%20smartphone%20to%20the%20very%20largest%20and%20now%20the%20fastest%20network%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20CNBC%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20also%20broadened%20Apple's%20reach%20beyond%20major%20cities%20through%20carrier%20partnerships%20and%20reseller%20networks%2C%20helping%20it%20tap%20a%20wider%20customer%20base%20as%20local%20rivals%20gained%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20China%20business%20has%20also%20grown%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20from%20about%20%2459%20billion%2C%20or%20about%2025%25%20of%20revenue%20in%202015%2C%20to%20about%20%2464%20billion%20in%202025%2C%20cementing%20it%20as%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20biggest%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20topped%20China's%20smartphone%20market%20last%20year%2C%20holding%20about%2022%25%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECook%20managed%20a%20delicate%20balance%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226983%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Cook%20shaking%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20hand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6903979b0be9845f2dc56792%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224655%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20and%20other%20tech%20executives%20visited%20Tokyo%20this%20month%20with%20President%20Donald%20J.%20Trump%20to%20promote%20Japanese%20investment%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harnik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Apple%20to%20succeed%20in%20China%2C%20Cook%20had%20to%20walk%20a%20political%20tightrope%20between%20Washington%20and%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20Cook%20lobbied%20officials%20to%20emphasize%20the%20potential%20harm%20tariffs%20would%20cause%20to%20American%20consumers%20and%20businesses%2C%20framing%20Apple's%20success%20as%20integral%20to%20US%20economic%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20he%20engaged%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-narrowly-avoids-iphone-tariff-after-trumps-china-trade-deal-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariffs%20on%20Chinese%20imports%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20competition%20from%20the%20South%20Korean%20company%20Samsung%20Electronics.%20Trump%20later%20said%20Cook%20had%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20case%26quot%3B%20that%20tariffs%20would%20put%20Apple%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20against%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20trade%20regulators%20then%20approved%2010%20out%20of%2015%20tariff%20exemption%20requests%2C%20easing%20pressure%20on%20Apple's%20China-based%20supply%20chain.%20In%202025%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-trump-tariffs-china-liberation-day-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple's%20smartphones%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20electronics%20were%20also%20spared%20from%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Cook%20worked%20to%20maintain%20strong%20ties%20in%20China%2C%20even%20as%20US-China%20tensions%20escalated%20during%20the%202018%20trade%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20regularly%20met%20Chinese%20regulators%20and%20senior%20officials%2C%20and%20attended%20high-level%20forums%20such%20as%20the%20China%20Development%20Forum%20to%20reinforce%20Apple's%20position%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHe%20invested%20heavily%20in%20China's%20ecosystem%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225112%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Cook%20in%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e72603367066d7c296ef66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETed%20S.%20Warren-Pool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20didn't%20just%20rely%20on%20China%20to%20build%20Apple's%20products%20%E2%80%94%20he%20invested%20in%20the%20ecosystem%20to%20make%20that%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Apple%20invested%20%241%20billion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-things-to-know-about-didi-chuxing-2016-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DApple%2520is%2520investing%2520%25241%2520billion%2Cin%2520less%2520than%2520a%2520month.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDidi%20Chuxing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20the%20country's%20dominant%20ride-hailing%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20said%20the%20deal%20would%20help%20the%20company%20better%20understand%20China%2C%20its%20second-biggest%20market.%20The%20firm%20said%20Apple's%20investment%20was%20the%20largest%20ever%20investment%20in%20its%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20learn%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20business%20and%20the%20Chinese%20market%20beyond%20what%20we%20currently%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Apple%20has%20poured%20significant%20resources%20into%20China.%20In%202021%2C%20Tim%20Cook%20signed%20an%20agreement%20with%20Chinese%20officials%20worth%20about%20%24275%20billion%2C%20aimed%20at%20easing%20regulatory%20pressure%20on%20the%20company's%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20included%20commitments%20to%20invest%20in%20retail%20expansion%2C%20research%20and%20development%20centers%2C%20and%20renewable%20energy%20projects%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20The%20Information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20Cook%20told%20China's%20industry%20minister%20that%20Apple%20would%20keep%20investing%20in%20the%20country.%20Cook%20also%20unveiled%20plans%20for%20a%20%24101%20million%20new%20energy%20fund%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20China%20in%20March%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-china-apple-ceo-step-down-legacy-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776758566000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e71029a98bc8fdc096ccc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-china-apple-ceo-step-down-legacy-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A